    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Config
    Non-sensitive configuration that is stored in the swarm.
    Container
    A docker container, a running instance of an image.
    Container.LogStreams
    A container's log streams.
    Container.StopCondition
    The type of stop condition to wait for.
    Container.WaitForStopResult
    The result of the Container.waitForStop(StopCondition) operation.
    ContainerAlreadyStartedException
    Thrown if the user attempts to start a container that is already started.
    ContainerCreator
    Creates a container.
    ContainerCreator.BindMountOptions
    Options that apply to bind mounts.
    ContainerCreator.CreateResult
    The result of creating a container.
    ContainerCreator.RestartPolicy
    Determines when the container should automatically restart.
    ContainerCreator.RestartPolicyCondition
    Determines when a container is restarted automatically.
    ContainerLogs
     
    ContainerNotFoundException
    Thrown if a referenced container does not exist.
    DockerClient
    A client of the Docker REST API.
    Image
    A docker image.
    ImageBuilder
    Builds an image.
    ImageNotFoundException
    Thrown if a referenced image does not exist.
    ImagePuller
    Pulls an image from a remote repository.
    ImagePusher
    Pushes an image to a remote repository.
    Node
    A docker node.
    Node.Availability
    Indicates if the node is available to run tasks.
    Node.Reachability
    Indicates if it is possible to communicate with the node.
    Node.State
    Indicates the overall health of the node.
    Node.Status
    The overall health of the node.
    Node.SwarmRole
    The role of the node within the swarm.
    Server
    A docker server.
    Swarm
    A docker swarm (cluster).
    Task
    A unit of work that executes on a node.
